    "body": "<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\n`vim.pack.update()` can crash with `attempt to concatenate field 'sha_target' (a nil value)` in `compute_feedback_lines_single`. When a lockfile entry has no `rev`, `do_update` sets `p.info.sha_target = nil`, and the subsequent `git_get_hash('*lockfile*', ...)` fallback error wasn't always surfaced through `p.info.err`, leaving the feedback renderer to concatenate nil.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nValidate `l_data.rev` early in the `lockfile` target branch and add a check in the feedback renderer so missing revisions are reported clearly instead of crashing the update.",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-11T18:15:42Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> When a lockfile entry has no `rev`\n\nCould you please elaborate on how the `rev=nil` situation occurred?\n\nThis should not happen, as lockfile is repaired on restart. So if this happens, it is the result of manual edit, which is prohibited. The relevant information about this problem and how to solve it would appear in `:checkhealth vim.pack`.",
